comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: There is a contemporary 1903 panorama taken by Martin Vaniman from the top of that chimney at right. It almost but not quite shows the Jubilee Dock on its left. Click through to the large size here - acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=412343

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: The Channel 7 building is not on the 1903 Vaniman panorama, and might provide a date for this photo,  since the 1912 Naval Stores warehouse is not built.  Guessing c.1905 ?
